import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['temperature'], bins=20, edgecolor='black')
    plt.xlabel('Temperature (°C)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of temperature in Seattle?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['pressure'])
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Atmospheric Pressure (hPa)')
    plt.title('How does the atmospheric pressure vary over time in Seattle?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    data['hour'] = data['date'].dt.hour
    data['day_night'] = data['hour'].apply(lambda x: 'Day' if 6 <= x < 18 else 'Night')
    avg_temp = data.groupby('day_night')['temperature'].mean()
    
    avg_temp.plot(kind='bar', rot=0)
    
    plt.title("What is the average temperature in Seattle during the day and night?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Day and Night")
    plt.ylabel("Average Temperature (°C)")
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
